.TH TTY 4 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ Drivers and Modules"
.\"
.\"
.SH NAME
.B TTY
\- @PACKAGE_TITLE@ (TTY)
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #include <sys/stropts.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/termios.h>
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B TTY
is provided by the
.BR "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ " ( @PACKAGE@ - @VERSION@ )
add-on package for
.BR "Linux Fast-STREAMS" .
The
.B @PACKAGE@
package contains header files and the following
.IR STREAMS (4)
modules and drivers:
.\"
.SS Drivers
.PP
.B @PACKAGE@
provides the following
.I STREAMS
pseudo-device drivers:
.TP
.BR ptm (4)
.I STREAMS
Pseudo-Terminal Master Driver.
.TP
.BR pts (4)
.I STREAMS
Pseudo-Terminal Slave Driver.
.TP
.BR pty (4)
.I STREAMS
Pseudo-Terminal Master and Slave Drivers.
.\"
.SS Modules
.PP
.PP
.B @PACKAGE@
provides the following
.I STREAMS
pushable modules:
.TP
.BR pckt (4)
.I STREAMS
Packet Mode Module.
.TP
.BR ptem (4)
.I STREAMS
Pseudo-Terminal Emulation Module.
.TP
.BR ttcompat (4)
.I STREAMS
TTY Compatibility Module.
.TP
.BR ldterm (4)
.I STREAMS
Line Discipline for Terminals.
.\"
.SS Devices
.PP
.B @PACKAGE@
provides the following
.I STREAMS
device drivers:
.\"
.\"
.\".SH NOTICES
.\".PP
.\"
.\"
.SH DEVICES
.PP
.TP
.I /dev/ptyXX
.TP
.I /dev/ptmx
.TP
.I /dev/ptm
.TP
.I /dev/ptsXX
.\"
.\"
.SH MODULES
.PP
.TP
.RI \(lq pckt \(rq
.TP
.RI \(lq ptem \(rq
.TP
.RI \(lq ttcomapt \(rq
.TP
.RI \(lq ldterm \(rq
.\"
.\"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR grantpt (3tty),
.BR ptsname (3tty),
.BR unlockpt (3tty),
.BR ldterm (4),
.BR pckt (4),
.BR ptc (4),
.BR ptem (4),
.BR ptm (4),
.BR ptmx (4tty),
.BR pts (4tty),
.BR pty (4),
.BR ttcompat (4),
.BR streams_mkdev (8),
.BR test-tty (8).
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
The
.B TTY
modules and drivers provided by the
.B @PACKAGE@
add-on package are compatible with
.I SVR 4.2 MP
and implementations based on
.I SVR 4.2 MP
including
.IR Solaris \(rg
and
.IR UnixWare \(rg,
with the following portability considerations:
.IP \(em \w'\(em\(em'u
.IP \(em
.IP \(em
.IP \(em
.IP \(em
.\"
.\"
.\".SH CONFORMANCE
.\".PP
.\"
.\"
.SH HISTORY
.PP
A Terminal Subsystem based on
.I STREAMS
initially appeared in
.IR "SVR 4" .
.PP
.B @PACKAGE@
was started as a separate package from
.BR Linux Fast STREAMS
in August 2006.
